# CostPilot AI — Environment Variables

Copy to `.env.local` and fill in values.

## Required for local demo (works out of the box)

No env vars required. The app runs in **demo mode** with a local JSON database at `.data/costpilot.json`.

## Supabase (production auth + database)

```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key
```

## Custom SMTP / Email Provider (Optional)

```env
# Choose one of: resend, sendgrid, smtp
EMAIL_PROVIDER=
EMAIL_FROM="CostPilot AI <noreply@costpilotsai.com>"

# If using Resend:
RESEND_API_KEY=

# If using SendGrid:
SENDGRID_API_KEY=

# If using Zoho / Custom SMTP:
SMTP_HOST=
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=
SMTP_PASS=
```

Run migration: paste `supabase/migrations/001_initial_schema.sql` into Supabase SQL editor.

Create storage bucket `blueprints` (private).

Enable Google OAuth in Supabase Auth settings (optional).

## Google Gemini (blueprint vision extraction)

```env
GEMINI_API_KEY=AIzaSy...
```

Without this key, the app uses heuristic extraction (still produces estimates).

## Inngest (async job queue — optional in demo)

```env
INNGEST_EVENT_KEY=...
INNGEST_SIGNING_KEY=...
```

In demo mode, analysis runs synchronously in the API route.

## Stripe (subscriptions)

```env
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...
STRIPE_PRICE_STARTER=price_...
STRIPE_PRICE_PRO=price_...
```

Create products in Stripe Dashboard:
- Starter — $49/mo — 15 estimates
- Pro — $99/mo — 100 estimates

Webhook endpoint: `https://your-domain.com/api/webhooks/stripe`

Events: `checkout.session.completed`, `customer.subscription.updated`, `customer.subscription.deleted`

## Vercel deployment

1. Connect GitHub repo to Vercel
2. Add all env vars above
3. Deploy — Inngest auto-registers at `/api/inngest`

## Validation script

```bash
npm run validate -- path/to/plan.pdf TX Austin
```
